eu.excitement.entailment.core.representation.parsetree

Class DependencyRelation

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.excitement.entailment.core.representation.parsetree.DependencyRelation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class DependencyRelation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    [DELETEME_LATER: Imported from BIUTEE 2.4.1 with no modification - but note that the DependencyRelationType is a new type] dependency relation is the relation between a node in the dependency parse tree and its parent. For example: subject, object.

    The relation is represented as a string, and as a canonical representation by DependencyRelationType.

    This class is IMMUTABLE

    Author:
    Asher Stern
